# CRUD Integration Plan — MangaManagementSystem (Revised)

## Background

The project is a 3-layer ASP.NET Core Web API (DataAccess → Business → WebApi). Auth (JWT) and User CRUD are already implemented.
The pattern is:
- **DataAccess**: Generic `IRepository<T>` / `Repository<T>` + EF Core `MangaDbContext`
- **Business**: `IXxxService` / `XxxService` + AutoMapper `Profile` + DTOs (Request + Response)
- **WebApi**: `[ApiController]` controllers, `BaseResponse` wrapper, Swagger annotations, role-based `[Authorize(Policy="...")]`

This plan covers the remaining **16 entities** grouped into **10 feature domains** and adds **file-retrieval routes** nested under each owning resource.

---

## Design Decisions (Resolved)

> [!NOTE]
> **File retrieval skipped**: All `FileAsset`-backed download/URL-generation endpoints are **out of scope** for this iteration. The CRUD for `FileAsset` records themselves (metadata only) will be included where referenced, but no pre-signed URL or proxy-download routes will be created.

> [!NOTE]
> **ChapterPage belongs to Chapter only**: `ChapterPage` should have **no relationship with `Manuscript`**. The current entity and DbContext incorrectly include a `ManuscriptId` FK. This will be corrected as part of this plan (entity fix + EF migration).

> [!NOTE]
> **Annotation belongs to Manuscript**: `Annotation` links to a `Manuscript` via `ManuscriptId` + `PageNo`. This means an editor can annotate a specific page of a specific manuscript submission. The chapter context is derived via `Manuscript → Chapter`. No schema change needed here — the existing model is correct.

> [!NOTE]
> **Soft-delete only**: All DELETE operations set `DeletedAt = UtcNow`. No hard deletes anywhere in the system.

